      • analyseUseCycle

        public static boolean analyseUseCycle(String filePath)
                               throws IOException
        This method analyse the use of the CYCLE sentence in the file. It is used in loops to avoid making a certain sentence, so that it continues to iterate to the next element. With they use, the code is more efficient.
        Parameters:
        filePath - of the file analysed
        Returns:
        boolean about the answer to the use of CYCLE sentence
        Throws:
        IOException - in case something wrong with intput/output file

      • analyseGoodComment

        public String analyseGoodComment(String filePath)
                          throws IOException
        This method check if all comments are good. This is: 1.- the functions are commented after or before the declaration. 2.- the variables are commented after or before the declaration. 3.- the subrutines are commented after or befor the declaration. 4.- the three first or more lines of a file are commented.
        Parameters:
        filePath - of the file analysed
        Returns:
        the paragraph to add to the pdf file
        Throws:
        IOException - in case something wrong with intput/output file
